          <td valign="top" nowrap><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=279&amp;sid=2c98f5027e08a090ef3be427292d8c82"><img src="templates/ezHyperShadow/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>  
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td colspan="2">
            <hr />
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td colspan="2"><span
class="postbody">First, I would  like to tell the whole story on the situation.  When you kill an X4 mob, about 50% of the time (in our experience so far) a metal chest drops, and about 50% of the time a wooden chest drops.  I believe that the contents of the metal chest and the wooden chest will be identical, aside from 1 extra loot in the metal chest, which will be an "uber" loot.  These are always very good items, seem to always have an effect of some sort, great stats, etc.  I don't think that any specific mob we have killed so far has an affinity to dropping any particular uber loot or set of uber loots like in eq1, it seems to be a shared pool.  That being said, even in the wooden boxes there is always both  some Tier 5 rares for making stuff you can make out of harvestable rares, AND some other as-of-yet unidentified tradeskills items, which I have been assured will be craftable into even better items than the "uber" loots.  The value of T5 rares like Ebon and Rubies cannot be dismissed, as Ebon makes the best armor currently known aside from uber loots, and the Rubies can be used to upgrade any level 40-49 spell or skill to adept 3.  However, it will only be so long before we have made all of the Ebon weapons and Armor that we want, and everybody has all of their adept 3's worth making.  Generally we see 1-3 T5 rares, and 1-3 of the other tradeskill items per kill, regardless of chest type.  On the kill posted on the news page there was no other tradeskills items, just some T5 rares, but that is  quite uncommon.  Mind you that currently nobody has recipes, leads on where to get them, or any additional information on crafting these items to my knowledge.  So, on to the Poll.  Do you believe that every single ubermob-style groupx4 encounter on a long respawn time should drop a metal chest 100% of the time?
<br />

<br />
My personal view on this is that they should, just because it's good for morale.  Kill the ubermob, pass out the uber loot.  And if these items pale in comparrison to the craftable items, then what's the harm?  Especially right now since we can't actually make the other items.  On the other hand, this team seems to have a very good idea of the "big picture" and I have learned to put some faith in them.  Regardless of which, I'm tired of getting wooden chests.  I don't believe that the end result of a successful ubermob kill should ever be dissapointment, and,  as misguided or misinformed as we may be in feeling that way, that's how we feel when we get a wooden chest.
<br />

<br />
I also welcome discussion on the matter.<br />_________________<br />Alloria Mistwave
<br />
Level 50 Templar
<br />
EQ2 Fires of Heaven Leader
<br />
Site Administrator</span><span
class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Requiem on Sat Feb 12, 2005 8:14 pm; edited 3 times in total</span></td>
