          <td colspan="2"><span
class="postbody">I agree that the team that is behind the scene at EQ2 is doing a great job.  They have added great new content, quests, and the graphics are just stellar.  I read the eq2 forums everyday and people complain about everything.  These Devs are weeding out the crap complaints and nailing a lot of the adjustments that need to go into affect for the majority of the populous to be happy.   
<br />

<br />
The toughest part being a player and leader is awarding people for their efforts.  This is with loot in EQ2 (and any MMO really).  When a challenge takes 24 people to coordinate their lives and skill on the game to defeat - a special reward is needed.   They rares now come from any named (non raid etc) and the 18 million harvesters, soon enough what Allo says will be true.  Everyone will be in full rare armor, have the spells/skills upgraded... and the x4 mob will only award 1 decent item 50% of the time.  Hardly motivational when you see that your chance of scoring a rare item is upwards of 100 raid mob kills to get 1 piece (50% metal chest, 24 people, 50% chance you can even use it).
<br />

<br />
Some might think my post was harsh, pissy, or extreme but I personally like to motivate people and award items for their time and effort.  It gets a bit hard when you have little to nothing to give to 30-40 hungry mouths.<br />_________________<br />Noah
<br />
50th Guardian
