          <td colspan="2"><span
class="postbody">Naz, your starting to see more rares in the world because more people are getting to the level that they can harvest those rares more easily. not because they are dropping more. 
<br />

<br />
Also, the FBSS is a bad example, as that was a single group fight. Didn't take 24 people to beat the Ghoul Lord.
<br />

<br />
Raid loot is always a touchy subject, because on one side of the extreme spectrum, you want to somehow reward everyone that goes to a raid with something, but for obvious reasons that can't happen. So your stuck somewherein the middle, and its a fine line that SOE walks on when dealing with loot.
<br />

<br />
My opinion is not that they should drop 100% of the time, but possibly even more rare, but with the loot tables changed. Make wooden chests the normal thing, but increase the quality of the loot inside of them substantially. Make Metal chests the end all Loot that is the BEST!
<br />

<br />
In a way this happened in EQ1 with the end of zone boss raid mobs. Make Quarm the Metal chest, and make the other gods the wooden chests.
<br />

<br />
By doing this, it will control the flood of "UBER" items into the game, but also award guilds with more quantity of loot that they wouldn't piss on either from the Wooden chests.<br />_________________<br />20 Bruiser / 23 Conjuror
