<br />

<br />
RvR is what drive mmo games. you put in more effort and man hours taking on higher challenging content, you get better gear. Its that simple. Atm a guy on our server named kett is running around in full ebon crafted armor, which is the best in game atm, all due to harvesting like crazy, and not a small amount of node jumping, I'm pretty sure he's been on less raids then any of our members, by an order of magnitude, yet is better armored,  all from doing an activity that has zero risk. This is wrong.
<br />

<br />
As for shared loot tables. it just lazy. Make up a bunch of uber stuff and put it into a global table and not worry about tailoring it or creating any lore behind it. What should be happening is that every uber mob should stop dropping those useless junk items they do, they are stupid. Instead they should be dropping 2 uber items, 1 from a common loot table which all ubers share, and one from a loot table specific to that mob. This will create more incentice to hit certain mobs for their specific loot. Once that loot is no longer needed by people and is rotting, will we still hit the mob? Maybe for the global loot but probably not. And you know what? thats ok, because it gives the next guild along a chance to play with the mob and gain from it in the case of non instanced ubers.<br />_________________<br />Faille
