        <tr>
          <td colspan="2"><span
class="postbody">One thing I will say that I miss is having that loot attached to a mob, not becasue of the predictability, but becasue of the uniqueness.
<br />

<br />
In original EQ you could see someone witha  piece of loot and say to yourself that they killed so and so (unless you were on FV of course then sky, or your bank roll, was the limit). I rememeber the first time I saw a BoW and thought that it was amazing, and then afterwards reading about how difficult the encounter to obtain that was I had a certain respect for tanks I saw carrying one.
<br />

<br />
However, with that being said, I think the very nice "legendary" loot should be extremely rare...I mean like no more then once every few months should it drop.
<br />

<br />
I was never a player who was the only one to hold a specific piece of loot, but I sure wish I had the opportunity since it would have been cool to strut it around.
<br />

<br />
By making a random pool of loot that could drop off of any high level mob they take away that very cool (for me at least) flavor.
<br />

<br />
Alot of good ideas here for certain, but I would still be careful to get what you ask for since if the rare loot dropped predictably you may run out of reasons to play this game faster then you would like.
<br />

<br />
Call me crazy but EQ1 would not have been the same if King Tormax dropped a Mask of the Dragon Slayer and Vox dropped a CoF. I like how items tell a history of your characters past.
<br />

<br />
That is also btw why I think attunable items are so fantastic.
<br />

<br />
Guess that went on a little longer then planned :p
<br />

<br />
Naz</span><span
class="gensmall"></span></td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </td>
